Apparently my current photos just aren't a painterly enough style in terms 
of lighting for this app to be useful or even all that entertaining. I 
think if I were doing more posed photography right now it could be fun, but 
seems like a lot of work to get anywhere close to a good result. If it 
started with a tutorial, or even had a good link for what kind of 
photography or lighting conditions create the best results I'd give it at 
least another star for being user-friendly. As-is, it's like clicking 
through purchased pre-sets collections for Photoshop without any knowledge 
of how to get into altering things in detail yourself.

I love impressionist art. Over the years, I've experimented with many applications designed to process photos to look like paintings. Nothing has even come close to Artista Impresso. In addition to its superior processing, the detail feature that allows you to focus in on certain features for more resolution is the critical trick to creating perfect images.
Transforms your images, whether photographs or digital art into classic impressionist style art, interface and controls so easy to use! One of the best art apps I've found so far!
